comments.body: We ran this today, and while it didn't break anything, we're still seeing the errors in the logs about `django.request Not Found: /websocket/`. That said, it looked like live job updates might be happening - so maybe the log messages are not tightly coupled to the problem . . . I'm going to hold this PR until we have some EEs and can gather more data.

Job updates are still not happening. If you kick off a job, you see the `Waiting for updates` message as long as you stay on the Jobs page, long after the job has failed (or succeeded). To see the actual output, you have to go back to `Jobs` and then select the individual job.
